<h1>@HI{{ka}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@HI{{ka}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{ka}}</strong> at the end of a sentence indicates a question, for example:
<ul>
<li> a simple question
<li> a question of the form "how about"
<li> a rhetorical question
<li> anger or censure
<li> indicates that someone is talking to himself
</ul>
</p>

<p>
Within a sentence, <strong>@HI{{ka}}</strong> can indicate doubt or uncertainty, for example:
<ul>
<li> a choice of the form "whether or not"
<li> uncertainty about a state or reason: "I wonder"
<li> following an interrogative word indicates such meanings as "anyone, anything, someone, something"
<li> following other particles, indicates uncertainty or doubt
</ul>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{ka}}</strong> also appears in the idiomatic expression <strong>@HI{{ka}}</strong> ... @HI{{nai uchi ni}}.
</p>

